--- !u!114 &969142266
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 969142261}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5dfa885c46c8cec4aab2730db202ba84, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  dialogue:
    name: Friendly Monster
    sentences:
    - 'Hi there traveller! My name is... well, I''ve been down here for so long,
      that I can''t even remember... '
    - Well, that doesn't matter I suppose. What's your name?
    - Hmm? Okay, it's fine - you don't need to tell me. I probably won't remember
      it in a few minutes anyway...
    - Well, I'm guessing this is your first time down here? Let me tell you how everything
      works
    - 'Firstly - you travel by map. To move from one node to another, you click on
      the next icon in front of you '
    - 'Remember:

      Heart = healing herb

      Chest = ingredient

      Monster
      Icon = combat '
    - 'Once you land on an ingredient or health node, the item placed there automatically
      goes into your inventory. You can use these during combat  '
    - 'You can access your inventory by pressing the "Journal" icon in the bottom
      right of the screen. '
    - 'Once you land on a combat node, you will be transported to a turn based combat
      sequence with a terrifying monster!! '
    - During combat, watch the wooden board at the top of the screen to see when
      its your turn, how much damage you took, and how much damage the monster does
      to you
    - 'The "Cook" button accesses your ingredient inventory - here you will select
      an item to deal more damage. '
    - 'The "Heal" button accesses your health herb inventory - here you can select
      a healing item. Note: healing counts as a turn '
    - Once you use an item, it will be gone from your inventory
    - 'IMPORTANT: If you die during combat, all of your progress will be erased,
      and you will have to restart from the point AFTER the tutorial battle. '
    - 'Your objective is to make your way through the map, fighting as many monsters
      as you can to gain more powerful ingredients, and eventually defeat the final
      boss to complete the first chapter.  '
    - Okay, you got all that?
    - ...
    - Still a man of few words I see
    - Before I forget - the monsters down here were human once, just like me. Once
      you die down here, you can't leave. Be kind to them
    - 'Okay! Let''s go! I''ll be your first opponent. if you''d like me to repeat
      anything, just press "Start" again! Otherwise, press "Continue" to go to the
      Map! '
